ns, love remains a neglected topic within Western philosophy. With its new interpretation of Antigone and related readings of Irigaray, Kristeva, and Ettinger, Antigone's Sisters aims to identify some of the reasons for this forgetting of love, and to show that it is only love that can bring peace to our ethically disrupted world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAntigone (Mythological character). 0aFemininity (Philosophy). 0aLove. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Feminist Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848275040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482750423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438482750/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles